To get this copy to work. You need to do this.

1. Don´t install every product/module. You will not use a fraction of them. Look below to find the necessary modules.

2. Replace the JS0GROUP.dll file that you find somwhere in the installation-directory with the file you find in the crack-directory.

3. During installation you are asked where to put the enviroment-files. I created a directory called CATenv for these files. Rename the CATIA_P3_V5R14B14.B14 to CATIA_P3_V5R14B14.txt

Catia will not find the enviroment file.


You now have a working copy of CATIA v5r14. CATIA is the world leading 3D CAD program.

I used a program called DVD Decrypter to burn these files to a cd. Just make sure you don't use the .cue files. You want to open up DVD Decrypter and then open the actual image file.

After you burn the files to cd's just load disc 1 and install wizard should start up.

As for installing the program refer to the comments made by trollkarlen.
thanx a lot but during installation it gives me an error msg C:/.../local/temp/log file something like this and asks to contact administrator wat should i do???? plz help...

When you've downloaded the two cd's, you've got 4 files :  nameCD1.bin, nameCD1.cue, nameCD2.bin, nameCD2.cue.

To execute the .bin : 
Download a software named UltraISO. Go to Tools, mount on virtual lector. Select nameCD1.bin, click on 'Mount'. Open a windows explorer, a new virtual disk has appeared (on the side of C:, D: etc). Double click on it : you've open the content of the .bin. Copy-paste all in a new directory contentCD1. The same for nameCD2.bin, in contentCD2.

Double click on i4target.exe.

Then double click on setup.exe of the contentCD1 : it launches the install. At the middle of it, asks for inserting the CD2. Copy-paste the content of contentCD2 in contentCD1.bin directory (when asks, no remplace files but save both with name file(2)). Finish the install. 

Launch Catia. Says that miss the license file. Close it. Open the directory contentCD1, directory crack, copy the file named JS0GROUP.dll y paste it in C://..../Dassault Systemes/B16/intel_a/code/bin.

Launch Catia : it works!!

Hope this will help you ;)
Don't forget helping the others an other time, and everybody will be happy!!
